    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Bar Graph 1: Landscape of Arts Education Nonprofits\"\nauthor: \"Steven Todd McIntyre II\"\ndate: \"2026-02-23\"\nruntime: shiny\nformat: \n  dashboard:\n    embed-resources: true\n    theme: minty\n    output:\n      orientation: columns\nexecute:\n  warning: false\n  message: false\n  echo: false\n---\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n# Overview\n\n## Column\n**How useful can NTEE Codes be in Studying Nonprofits?**\n\nThis dashboard will explore United States nonprofit organizations that are coded as \"A25\" in the National Taxonomy of Exempt Organizations (NTEE), a coding scheme that describes kinds of nonprofit organizations. \"A25\" is defined by the Urban Institute as \"Organizations that provide informal arts educational programming and/or instruction but do not grant diplomas or degrees; or which offer services regarding the arts to educational institutions or to public entities involved in education.\" Using data from the [Urban Institute's Business Master File (BMF)](https://urbaninstitute.github.io/nccs/datasets/bmf/), I explore the kinds of organizations that use A25 \n\n# Visualization 1: A25 Word Count\n\n## Column\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-1ef31a9af17028b4b043\" style=\"width:100%;height:406px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-1ef31a9af17028b4b043\">{\"x\":{\"data\":[{\"orientation\":\"v\",\"width\":[341,66,168,957,59,232,1842,314,379,52,51,83,49,161,68,53,80,174,57,66,106,266,45,147,657,45,72,182,55,96,522,91,76,45,56,307,48,98,65,53,164,405,164,114,52,98,59,52,91,110],\"base\":[43.549999999999997,17.550000000000001,36.549999999999997,48.549999999999997,14.550000000000001,39.549999999999997,49.549999999999997,42.549999999999997,44.549999999999997,6.5499999999999998,5.5499999999999998,23.550000000000001,4.5499999999999998,33.549999999999997,19.550000000000001,9.5500000000000007,22.550000000000001